'''Gifu Prefecture Machikado Art and History Museums''' (岐阜県まちかど美術館・博物館) is a cultural promotion project organized by the Cultural Heritage Division of Gifu Prefecture.
The official name is '''Machikado Art and History Museums'''.
== Overview == The project supports activities to make various cultural assets and artworks owned by individuals and organizations in [[:en:Gifu Prefecture|Gifu Prefecture]] widely accessible to the public. It registers museums and galleries capable of collaborating with this initiative as "Machikado Art and History Museums."
The registered museums and galleries vary in scale, ranging from prefectural facilities like the [[:en:Gifu Prefectural Museum|Gifu Prefectural Museum]] and the [[:en:Museum of Fine Arts, Gifu|Gifu Prefectural Museum of Art]] to privately managed facilities displaying personal collections.
This project began in 1991. The first registered museum was the {{ill|Nakasendō Mini Museum|ja|中山道ミニ博物館|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakasendō Mini Museum|qq=}} in [[:en:Tarui, Gifu|Tarui, Gifu]], but it was delisted in October 2024<ref name="">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nisimino.com/nisimino/person/25_index_msg.shtml |title=Connecting History to the Present: Director of the Nakasendō Mini Museum|publisher=Nishimino Regional Portal Site |accessdate=2022-05-05}}</ref><ref name="nakasendō">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pref.gifu.lg.jp/uploaded/attachment/256242.pdf |title=Nakasendō Mini Museum (Machikado Art and History Museums) |format=PDF |publisher=Gifu Prefecture |accessdate=2022-05-05}}</ref>. As of October 16, 2024, there are 97 registered facilities<ref name="gifu">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pref.gifu.lg.jp/page/393639.html |title=Machikado Art and History Museums |publisher=Gifu Prefecture |accessdate=2024-11-01}}</ref>.
